The paper discusses the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in classifying images, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the concept of adversarial examples, which are relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study involves human subjects, which suggests a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the findings for both human and machine cognition, which could be relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
